cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DS

The paper deals with the detection of groups in complex networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as the paper specifically mentions the relevance of group detection in large social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category, as the paper presents a new algorithm for group detection. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category, as the paper deals with the analysis and control of complex networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category, as the paper compares the proposed algorithm with other state-of-the-art approaches using rigorous evaluation metrics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category, as the paper presents a new algorithm for group detection that has near ideal complexity.
